President Obama spoke with Prime Minister Cameron of the United Kingdom, President Komorowski of Poland, and Chancellor Merkel of Germany regarding Russia's violation of Ukrainian sovereignty. They expressed their concern and stressed the need for dialogue between Ukraine and Russia, with international facilitation if necessary. The leaders also emphasized the importance of unity within the international community in support of international law and the Government of Ukraine. They pledged to provide financial assistance to Ukraine for urgently needed reforms and agreed to continue coordinating closely. The President reaffirmed the United States' commitment to security and democracy in Eastern Europe.